Ask HN: Has anyone successfully played Tic-Tac-Toe with an LLM?
text: I tried to get both GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 to play Tic-Tac-Toe and both failed absolutely. Half the time they declared victory or defeat too early, made invalid moves, and let me cheat without questioning it. The other half of the time the moves they made seemed random and they always were easily defeatable. Has anyone else had similar experiences or have a prompt that has been more successful?

Ask HN: Does Spam “Work”?
text: Scrolling through hundreds of messages in my spam mailbox I have a tough time understanding who spam works for / upon. With all the spelling mistakes, broken links/images, unclear messages, I can’t fathom that there are people out there who see spam and think “oh I want to buy whatever this person is selling”. Am I crazy? Is there some other purpose for spam (other than the obvious phishing attempts which don’t seem to be as common as just plain junk spam)?
